# Architectural Components

## 1. Presentation Layer (Frontend)

The Presentation Layer provides the user interface and interacts with the backend using REST APIs.

### Responsibilities

* User Registration and Login
* Display Dashboard
* Search Stocks
* Buy and Sell Stocks
* Display Portfolio
* View Transaction History
* Visualize Stock Charts

### Technologies

* React.js
* HTML5
* CSS3
* Bootstrap / Tailwind CSS
* Axios

---

## 2. Application Layer (Backend)

The Backend processes user requests, performs business logic, communicates with the database, and integrates with external stock market APIs.

### Responsibilities

* User Authentication
* Portfolio Management
* Trading Simulation
* Stock Data Retrieval
* Transaction Processing
* REST API Development

### Technologies

* Node.js
* Express.js
* JWT Authentication
* Bcrypt Password Encryption

---

## 3. Data Layer

The Data Layer stores application data and retrieves stock market information from external providers.

### Database Tables / Collections

* Users
* Portfolio
* Transactions
* Stock Holdings

### External APIs

* Alpha Vantage API
* Finnhub API
* Twelve Data API

